Topic: Advanced Configuration – Choice Lists & Reference Fields


1. Why Advanced Configuration Matters

As an administrator, you must configure:
  Choice fields
  Reference fields

These fields help teams maintain accurate, high-quality data when recording issues or incidents.


2. Choice Lists vs Reference Lists
Choice Lists
  Marked by a dropdown arrow
  Options are stored on the same table (e.g., Incident categories)

Reference Lists
  Marked by a magnifying glass
  Options come from a different table
    Examples:
      Service table
      Configuration Item (CI) table
      Service Offering table

Reference fields are more powerful because they allow relationships between tables.